BRIEFING:
NORTHERLY FLOW CONTINUES TO SUPPORT A STABLE AND VERY DRY AIRMASS OVER MOST OF THE ISLAND CHAIN. THE LONE EXCEPTION IS WINDWARD BIG ISLAND, WHERE DIMINISHING LOW LEVEL MOISTURE WILL PRODUCE POCKETS OF MVFR CONDITIONS FROM LAUPAHOEHOE NORTHWARD TODAY. DRY AND STABLE NORTHEAST WINDS WILL PREVAIL TONIGHT INTO MONDAY, WITH SOME INCREASE IN SHOWER ACTIVITY POSSIBLE AROUND KAUAI NEAR SUNDOWN TOMORROW.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
